'''Yin Wood Pig also known as äđäšĨ''' (kinotoi (äđäšĨ), otsubokunoinoshishi (äđäšĨ), itsugai (äđäšĨ)) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|å­ååđēæŊ}}.

It is the 12th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|å­ååđēæŊ}}, preceded by {{ill|Jikotsu|ja|įēæ|lt=Jikotsu|lt_ja=įēæ}} and followed by {{ill|Besshi|ja|äļå­|lt=Besshi|lt_ja=äļå­}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|é°é―äščĄææģ|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=é°é―äščĄ}}, the element represented by the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|ååđē}} symbol {{ill|Etsu|ja|äđ}} signifies yin {{ill|Wood|ja|æĻ}}, while the element represented by the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|åäšæŊ}} symbol {{ill|Pig|ja|äšĨ}} signifies yin {{ill|Water|ja|æ°ī}}, establishing a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|äščĄææģ#įļįïžãããããïž|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=įļį}}, i.e. Water generates Wood).

